<BaseLayout lang="en" title="About — Dmitry Gladkikh">
  <article class="about">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p class="lead">
        C++ / Python developer, 3 years of experience in computer vision and engineering software.
        Based in Novosibirsk, open to remote, hybrid, and relocation.
      </p>

      <h2>How I got here</h2>
      <p>
        Started with C++ at university — simple console programs, basic algorithms.
        After graduating I took courses in Python and backend development (Django, DRF, PostgreSQL,
        Celery, Redis), then joined Aviaspetstest, where I still work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over three years I went from early template-matching tasks to designing full measurement
        systems — from low-level camera work to GUI and REST API.
      </p>

      <h2>What I'm interested in</h2>
      <p>
        Tasks at the intersection of code and physics: image processing algorithms, working with
        industrial hardware, optimizing for real FPS and memory constraints. When measurements
        from your code are used on a test bench and the outcome depends on it — that's the best
        feedback a developer can get.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside work I maintain my own infrastructure: a home GitLab on a mini-PC, VPN access
        via WireGuard, a CI/CD pipeline to production servers. My personal projects run on this —
        a CRM for the family business, a utility Telegram bot, experiments.
      </p>

      <h2>What I'm looking for</h2>
      <p>
        Long-term projects where I can influence product quality. Backend, computer vision,
        systems software — anything with a real engineering problem, not just shuffling JSON.
      </p>
      <p>
        Happy to talk — write on <a href="https://t.me/Midnight_Fruit">Telegram</a>
        or by <a href="mailto:dima.gladkikh.2016@mail.ru">email</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
